Class:        Cephalopoda
Habitat:      Shallow sea
Diet:         Carnivore
Lifespan:     1 years
Weight:       0.5 kg
Status:       Least Concern
Fact:         Can mimic 15+ different species including lionfish and flatfish

Name:         Blue Whale
Scientific:   Balaenoptera musculus
Class:        Mammalia
Habitat:      Ocean
Diet:         Carnivore (krill)
Lifespan:     80 years
Weight:       150000 kg
Status:       Endangered
Fact:         Largest animal ever known; heart is size of a small car

============================================================
  DISEASES & MEDICINE
============================================================

Disease:     Ebola
Type:        Viral
Pathogen:    Ebola virus
Transmission:Bodily fluids contact
Symptoms:    Fever, bleeding, organ failure
Treatment:   Monoclonal antibodies, supportive
Deaths/yr:   0.001M
Vaccine:     Yes (Ervebo for Zaire strain)
Discovered:  1976

Disease:     Polio
Type:        Viral
Pathogen:    Poliovirus
Transmission:Fecal-oral
Symptoms:    Paralysis in severe cases
Treatment:   No cure; supportive care
Deaths/yr:   0M
Vaccine:     Yes (near-eradicated)
Discovered:  1840

Disease:     Dengue
Type:        Viral
Pathogen:    Dengue virus
Transmission:Aedes mosquito
Symptoms:    Fever, severe joint pain, rash
Treatment:   Supportive care, fluids
Deaths/yr:   0.04M
Vaccine:     Yes (for previously infected)
Discovered:  1779

============================================================
  SCIENCE FACTS
============================================================

Domain:  Chemistry
Topic:   Avogadro's Number
Formula: N_A = 6.022×10²³ mol⁻¹
Note:    Number of atoms/molecules in one mole

Domain:  Physics
Topic:   Gravitational Force
Formula: F = Gm1m2/r²
Note:    Universal gravitation between all masses

Domain:  Physics
Topic:   Ohm's Law
Formula: V = IR
Note:    Voltage, current, resistance relationship in circuits

Domain:  Physics
Topic:   2nd Law of Thermodynamics
Formula: ΔS ≥ 0
Note:    Entropy always increases in isolated systems

Domain:  Physics
Topic:   Boyle's Law
Formula: P₁V₁ = P₂V₂
Note:    Pressure and volume inversely proportional at constant T

